text.tspan: a) Cut the leaf on a new coverslip with a fresh blade. b) Transfer the leaf section to a capsule containing some
Tissue-Tek OCT and align the leaf to ensure it remains straight.c) Place the capsule in contact with a metal at N2
temperature, ensuring the leaf remains straight. Fill the capsule with Tissue-Tek OCT.d) Transfer the capsule to a
beaker containing methylbutane under stirring and in contact with N2.e) Remove the capsule from the
methylbutane and place it in a cryostat at -20Â°C.
